{/* Card for feedback of previous crops */} Paddy Paddy is the crop from which rice is obtained. It grows well in warm places with plenty of water. Farmers usually grow it in muddy fields during the rainy season. Small plants are first grown in a nursery and then planted in fields filled with water. After a few months, when the grains become yellow and ripe, the crop is harvested and used as rice for food. wheat Wheat is a crop grown in cooler weather and needs much less water than paddy. It is mainly grown in the winter season. Seeds are directly sown in well-prepared fields.
